    management: ["Prescribe fluconazole 200 mg loading dose followed by 100-200 mg daily for 7-14 days for oropharyngeal disease", "For esophageal candidiasis: fluconazole 400 mg loading then 200-400 mg daily for 14-21 days", "For azole-refractory disease: prescribe itraconazole oral solution 200 mg daily or voriconazole 200 mg BID", "For echinocandin-eligible refractory cases: micafungin 150 mg IV daily or caspofungin 70 mg load then 50 mg IV daily", "Initiate secondary prophylaxis with fluconazole 100 mg daily in HIV patients until CD4 > 200 sustained", "Address predisposing factors: optimize glycemic control, reduce immunosuppression when possible, manage xerostomia", "For denture-associated candidiasis: prescribe miconazole denture lacquer or chlorhexidine soaks plus systemic therapy", "Consider therapeutic drug monitoring for voriconazole (target trough 1-5.5 μg/mL)"],
